The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 The CBI on Friday arrested the sub-post master of the Bagha Jatin post office on charges of corruption. Prafulla Mondal, 52, was arrested while he was taking Rs 1,000 as bribe from a person who wanted to encash a Kisan Vikas Patra for Rs 5,000. Mondal has been booked under the Prevention of Corruption Act.

 Unable to persuade four condemned prisoners to call off their hunger strike, the Presidency jail authorities are planning to shift them to more airy cells. The four, condemned to death along with Aftab Ansari in the American Center attack case, are on an indefinite hunger strike demanding fans in their cells. Deputy inspector-general of prisons Ramapada Bhattacharya said on Friday that the jail code did not allow the authorities to provide fans in the cells. 

 The body of a 50-year-old man was found floating in Laldighi, BBD Bag, on Friday. It was noticed by passersby, who informed police. Another body of a man was found on the Lenin Sarani footpath around 8.30 am on Friday. 

 Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee will flag off Air India?s non-stop flight from Calcutta to London at NSC Bose Airport on Saturday afternoon. Union minister for aviation Praful Patel and Lok Sabha Speaker Somnath Chatterjee will attend the programme. The flight, on the Delhi-Dhaka-Calcutta-London route, will run on Tuesdays, Thursdays and Saturdays.

 A fire broke out at a medicine shop near the air-conditioned market in Baguiati on Friday afternoon. The blaze was noticed by local residents. Two tenders brought it under control within half-an-hour.

 Sridhar Bagari, a lawyer at Calcutta High Court, moved a PIL on Friday demanding ?substantial compensation? for the family members of the convicts who had been hanged. A division bench of Justice A.K. Ganguly and Justice T.K. Dutt admitted the petition and asked the state government and the Centre to file affidavits stating their stand in this regard. The matter will come up for hearing after four weeks. 

 The lawyers at the city civil and sessions court observed a ceasework on Friday, demanding upgrade in the facilities for litigants and lawyers on the compound. The lawyers at the Alipore court will observe a ceasework on Saturday and Monday for a similar reason.

 The state government on Friday sought three weeks to inform the court what steps it had taken to improve the condition of Liluah Rescue Home. Following a report on the state of affairs at the home by the state human rights commission, a division bench of the high court had asked the government to upgrade the facilities there.

 An audio-visual quiz on Satyajit Ray, his films and other works has been organised by Ekhon Satyajit, a Bengali quarterly, at Nandan. The history department of Calcutta University won the contest, while the first and second runners-up were Jadavpur University?s film studies department and Roopkala Kendra.

 Kanika Oraon, 38, was killed by husband Bachchu at their Titagarh residence, on the northern fringes of the city, on Thursday night. Police said a quarrel broke out between the two after Bachchu accused Kanika of having an extra-marital affair. Bachchu, in custody, has admitted to the crime.

